{"lemma":"بَتُولُ","slug":"بَتُولُ","root":"ب.ت.ل","root_slug":"ب-ت-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ت-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1733"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"A female given name."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Mary Mother of Jesus."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Fatima daughter of Muhammad."},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"chaste, virgin"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pure"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a female given name"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *batūl-. Compare Hebrew בְּתוּלָה (bəṯulá, “chaste (woman)”), Ugaritic 𐎁𐎚𐎍𐎚 (btlt), Aramaic בְּתוּלְתָּא (bəṯūltā)."},"ipa":["/ba.tuːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1733","headword_ar":"بَتُولٌ","root":"btl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shoot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an offset, of a palm-tree, cut off from its mother-tree, and independent thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiylapN","text_ar":"بَتِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, T, S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiylN","text_ar":"بَتِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A virgin, that is cut off from husbands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman that withholds herself from men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is cut off from men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no desire for them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor need of them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) and, with the art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to the Virgin Mary; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiylN","text_ar":"بَتِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) with the art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is applied also to Fátimeh, the daughter of Mohammad, because she was separated from the [other] women of her age and nation by chasteness and excel-lence and religion and [other] grounds of pretension to respect: (Ahmad Ibn-Yahyà, T, K: *) or it signifies, (S,) or signifies also, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman detached from worldly things, and devoted to God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiylN","text_ar":"بَتِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiylapN","text_ar":"بَتِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn- 'Abbád, K.)"}],"source_refs":["As","T","S","M","K","TA"]}]}}